713932f-a.text:
West 57th Street, west from a point slightly to the east of Eleventh Avenue and across same to the North (Hudson) River. These two views show opposite sides of this thoroughfare, being the south side and north side respectively. Buildings appearing across the foreground corners are on the north side of the Avenue and cover
collectively the 56th to 58th Streets area.
October 3, 1933.
Views 1 and 2
P. L. Sperr

710738f-a.text:
Eleventh Avenue, east side, from 58th to 57th Streets, showing the Empire State Building (Fifth Avenue at 34th Street) in
the background.

May 8, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.

713933f-a.text:
West 57th Street (center, left to right), at Eleventh Ave. (left), as viewed in a northward direction from 56th Street and across the future site of the Sheffield Farms milk plant, showing the diagonal rock cut roadway of the New York Central Railroad tracks which will pass beneath this structure and continue in a northward direction to the 60th Street yards (center, background). Completion of this phase of the West Side Project will eliminate the use of the street bed of the Ave. for Railroad purposes as observed on the right at the base of the I.R.T. power plant between 58th and
59th Streets.
1937.
Gift of New York Central System
Publicity Bureau.

713934f-a.text:
West 57th Street (foreground), at the S.E. corner of Eleventh Ave. (extreme right), showing the ultra modern Sheffield Farms plant under construction and occupying the westerly portion of the 57th to 56th Street. Buildings appearing at the left will shortly be razed to permit expansion to the full 200 x 550 feet proposed. Note the rock cut roadbed of the New York Central Railroad beneath the steel, veering on a diagonal to emerge in the 60th Street yards on the far side of the Ave.
July 24, 1937.
Gift of New York Central System
Publicity Bureau.

713936f-a.text:
West 57th Street, west from a point east of Eleventh Ave., and across same to the North (Hudson) River. Under construction on the left is a building at the S.E. corner of this street and Eleventh Ave. In the background appears Pier No. 97.
November 25, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.

733565f-a.title: West Side Improvement Project.
733565f-a.text:
West Side Improvement Project: A northward view from under West 57th Street, showing the rock bed of the enclosed Railroad tracks progressing towards the 60th Street yards on the westerly side of Eleventh Ave., after paralleling the easterly side of same from 35th Street. At the left appears the I.R.T. power house on the west side of Eleventh Ave., between 58th and 59th Streets.
July 24, 1937.
Gift of New York Central System
Publicity Bureau.

713935f-b.text:
West 57th Street, at the N.E. corner of Eleventh Avenue (left), showing a gasoline station at this location. Surrounding same are tenements on 57th Street (right) and Eleventh Avenue which are gone in view No. 2, as the diagonal underpass of the New York Central Railroad is being cut thru here so as to pass under Eleventh Avenue to the 59th Street yards.

View No. 3 shows this phase with 58th Street being bridged in the foreground.

Note the I.R.T. power house at the extreme left. For further views of this Railroad improvement, see the files under the West Side
Improvement Project.

October 3, 1933
Views 2 & 3: May 21, 1936.
